    <h1> About StormWater </h1>
    <h2> What does Stormwater do to the world? </h2>
    <h4> Storm Water is a problem to the world, because water that comes from the rain, drops down
      <br/>
    then carries polution which cause storm waterpolution. </h4>
      <br/>
      <img src="http://www.miwaterstewardship.org/Portals/0/images/water-oil.stormdrain.322px.jpg">
      <br/>
      <caption> Effect on stormwater polution. </caption>
      <br/>
      <h4> The stormwater can effect the world because when the polution goes down the drain, it
      <br/>
      will go to the ocean, (if the waste water treatment plant is full) then the sea animals will get infected by the pollution.
      <br/>
      Now sometimes when you eat fish, it could be infected by the pollution. This doesn't mean you can't eat sea food.
      <br/>
      Every year a tons of fish die of pollution and it is caused by us humans who litter. Don't litter when you are lazy,
      <br/>
      If we have people in our world that don't litter, just imagine how life would be! Clean fish, clean ocean, and less chance of global warming.
      <br/>
      Just think about the extintict animals and plants, all because of our garbage (and also killing) had lead to many extintictions of animals.
      <br/>
      Even if we had LAWS, littering will still be a thing because even if you break the law of littering and you have to pay, people are gonna
      <br/>
      litter because people are going to do it when no one is looking at them. Maybe some countries don't have laws about littering. That's why our
      <br/>
      world has many things extintict because of our garbage. We can stop this by putting more garbage cans so that people can put it in the garbage
      <br/>
      easily. If you are manager of the city, what would you do when there is a garbage problem?
      <br/>
    </h4>
